TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Comm Spawn
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
if not Spring.GetModOptions().commandertypes then GG.mission.ExecuteTriggerByName("Spawn Comm Fallback") else local teamID = 0 local teamInfo = teamID and select(7, Spring.GetTeamInfo(teamID)) if teamInfo and teamInfo.staticcomm then local commanderName = teamInfo.staticcomm local commanderLevel = teamInfo.staticcomm_level or 1 local commanderProfile = GG.ModularCommAPI.GetCommProfileInfo(commanderName) local startUnit = commanderProfile.baseUnitDefID
local x, z = 5000, 3580 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) local unitID = GG.DropUnit(startUnit, x, y, z, 0, teamID, _, _, _, _, _, GG.ModularCommAPI.GetProfileIDByBaseDefID(startUnit), teamInfo and tonumber(teamInfo.static_level), true) Spring.TransferUnit(unitID, 3) -- Gaia GG.mission.AddUnitGroup(unitID,"Comm") end end

TriggerLogic.Name: Transfer Gaia to Gaia
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Gaia") for unitID in pairs(units) do Spring.TransferUnit(unitID, Spring.GetGaiaTeamID(), false) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Force Start
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
Spring.SendCommands("info 0")
-- force start when testing from Mission Editor -- not needed if run from Chobby campaign (a widget will do this) if not Spring.GetModOptions().commandertypes then Spring.SendCommands("forcestart") end

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Learn the bare basics of playing Zero-K. Follow the provided instructions at each step.
TriggerLogic.Title: Complete Quick Tutorial

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
\255\255\255\0\Zoom the camera\008 to your \255\255\255\0\Glaives\008.
+ Pan the camera with \255\0\255\0\arrow keys\008, the \255\0\255\0\screen edge\008 or \255\0\255\0\middle mouse\008 button. + Zoom with \255\0\255\0\scrollwheel\008 or \255\0\255\0\Page Up and Page Down\008.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: Spring.SetGameRulesParam("tutorial_stage", 1)

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: if WG.CustomMarker then WG.CustomMarker.AddPoint("cameraTarget", 2420, 3580, "Zoom in here") end

TriggerLogic.Name: Comm to Gaia
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Comm") for unitID in pairs(units) do Spring.TransferUnit(unitID, Spring.GetGaiaTeamID(), false) end

TriggerLogic.Message:
\255\0\255\0\Left click\008 and drag a box to select your Glaives.
+ \255\0\255\0\Right click\008 on the ground to \255\255\255\0\move\008. + \255\0\255\0\Right click\008 enemies to \255\255\255\0\force fire\008. + Press \255\0\255\0\A\008 and left click on the ground to \255\255\255\0\attack move\008.
Destroy the enemy units to the right

TriggerLogic.Name: Set Stage 2
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: Spring.SetGameRulesParam("tutorial_stage", 2)

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: if WG.CustomMarker then WG.CustomMarker.RemovePoint("cameraTarget") WG.CustomMarker.AddPoint("selectGlaives", 2420, 3580, "Select your Glaives") end

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Kill Marker
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: if WG.CustomMarker then WG.CustomMarker.RemovePoint("selectGlaives") WG.CustomMarker.AddPoint("target1", 3200, 3580, "Destroy") end

TriggerLogic.Name: Set Stage 3
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: Spring.SetGameRulesParam("tutorial_stage", 3)

TriggerLogic.Message:
\255\0\255\0\Right click and drag\008 to draw a line formation.
(Make sure all your units are selected)

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Line Move Marker
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: if WG.CustomMarker then WG.CustomMarker.RemovePoint("selectGlaives") WG.CustomMarker.RemovePoint("target1") WG.CustomMarker.AddPoint("lineMove1", 3670, 3440, "Right-click, drag from here...") WG.CustomMarker.AddPoint("lineMove2", 4020, 3740, "...to here and let go") end

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Rescue Marker
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: if WG.CustomMarker then WG.CustomMarker.RemovePoint("lineMove1") WG.CustomMarker.RemovePoint("lineMove2") WG.CustomMarker.AddPoint("rescue", 5000, 3580, "Rescue") end

TriggerLogic.Name: Set Stage 4
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: Spring.SetGameRulesParam("tutorial_stage", 4)

TriggerLogic.Message: Destroy the Stinger and Ronin to the right to rescue your Commander.

TriggerLogic.Name: Remove Markers
